properties.description: Allow game clients to subtract from virtual currency balances via API.

properties.name: AllowNonUniquePlayerDisplayNames
properties.description: Allow players to choose display names that may be in use by other players, i.e. do not enforce uniqueness of display names. Note: if this option is enabled, it cannot be disabled later.

properties.name: AllowServerToDeleteUsers
properties.description: Allow game servers to delete player accounts via API.

properties.name: DisableAPIAccess
properties.description: Disable API access by returning errors to all API requests.

properties.name: DisplayNameRandomSuffixLength
properties.description: Display name randomly-generated suffix length.

properties.name: EnableClientIPAddressObfuscation
properties.description: Reduce the precision of IP addresses collected from players' devices before they are stored or used to estimate geographic locations.

properties.name: RequireCustomDataJSONFormat
properties.description: Require JSON format for data values associated with players, characters, inventories, and shared groups.

properties.name: UseExternalGameServerProvider
properties.description: Multiplayer game sessions are hosted on servers external to PlayFab.

properties.name: UseSandboxPayments
properties.description: Use payment provider's sandbox mode (if available) for real-money purchases. This can be useful when testing in-game purchasing in order to avoid being charged.

properties.name: City
properties.description: City of the geographic location.

properties.name: ContinentCode
properties.description: Two-character code representing the continent of geographic location.

properties.name: CountryCode
properties.description: Two-character ISO 3166-1 code representing the country of the geographic location.

properties.name: Latitude
properties.description: Latitude coordinate of the geographic location.

properties.name: Longitude
properties.description: Longitude coordinate of the geographic location.

properties.name: ParentEventId
properties.description: The ID of the previous event that caused this event to be created by hitting a trigger.

properties.name: ParentTriggerId
properties.description: The ID of the trigger that caused this event to be created.

properties.name: TriggeredEvents
properties.description: If true, then this event was allowed to trigger subsequent events in a trigger.
